TI-99 console ROMs are copyrighted and not included with this
software.  In order to run the emulator, you must find a way to obtain
them on your own.  See https://mrousseau.org/programs/ti99sim/ for
instructions.  ROM images in .bin format are known to be included in
the v9t9 and classic99 distributions.  The required ROM images is
typically named 994aROM.Bin.  It must be converted to .ctg format
using convert-ctg for use with ti99-sim.  The expected filename is
TI-994A.ctg.  The expected location is the current working directory
(.), ~/.ti99sim/roms, or PREFIX/share/ti99sim/roms.
